---
layout: base.njk
pageType: home
title: proofstone — engineering roadmaps where every milestone is a proof
description: Engineering roadmaps where every milestone is a proof — a verifiable artifact, not a keyword. Built for working engineers.
---
<section class="hero">
  <h1 class="hero__title">{{ site.tagline }}</h1>
  <p class="hero__sub">{{ site.thesisSub }}</p>
  <p class="hero__series">{{ site.seriesLine }}</p>
</section>

<section class="roadmaps" aria-label="Roadmaps">
  {% for r in liveRoadmaps %}
  <a class="card" href="/{{ r.slug }}/">
    <h2 class="card__title">{{ r.title }}</h2>
    <p class="card__tagline">{{ r.tagline }}</p>
    <p class="card__meta">
      <span class="badge badge--count">{{ r.milestones }} milestones</span>
      {% if r.star %}<span class="badge badge--star">★ on GitHub</span>{% endif %}
      <span class="card__go" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </p>
  </a>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section class="thesis">
  <h2>Why proof, not keywords</h2>
  <p>{{ site.thesis }}</p>
  <p class="thesis__contribute">
    The roadmap repositories are the source of truth — this site is the render layer.
    Contribute by opening a pull request on a roadmap's repo; the site rebuilds itself.
    <a href="{{ site.org }}" rel="noopener">github.com/proofstone →</a>
  </p>
</section>
